$interpreted: Puggi: Hmmmphhh!!!
Maeok: You're saying this mermaid and... bird, are yours? Do you have proof?
Sennosuke: Proof? I don't usually have that kind of stuff on hand, but if you need it...
Sennosuke: Hey! Show the arbiter proof!
Puggi: Mmmmmmmmph!!!
Sennosuke: Is that enough for you, arbiter?
Maeok: You—
Panther Chieftain: It's fine. You should really take better care of your things.
Sennosuke: Heh, yeah, I'll pay more attention in the future.
Sennosuke: Well, if that's all, then I should get going. Let's do tea soon!
Pang: Hands off!
Puggi: Hmmmph!!
Hestia: Mmmmmmmmph!!!
Pang: Don't worry, I'm here to save you!
Pang: Untie them! They're my friends, not your property!
Maeok: Juan-Yun, weren't you just saying you had to leave? Why are you back again so soon?
Juan-Yun: Arbiter, I'm sorry for barging in like this.
Juan-Yun: But lives are at stake! That mermaid is from Maple Lake, far away from here, and owes nothing to the honey badgers!
Juan-Yun: You're letting Sennosuke get away with kidnapping, plain and simple.
Tortoise Chieftain: ...Maple Lake? Sounds like Water-Sect land. Have you heard of it, Seahorse Chieftain?
Seahorse Chieftain: I know all Alliance lakes, big and small, but I've never heard of Maple Lake!
Sennosuke: Hmph. I bet Juan-Yun's just making it up! He saw a pretty girl and wants her for himself, the rascal!
Hestia: Mm! Mmmmph!!
Sennosuke: Everyone knows mermaids are a hot commodity.
Sennosuke: Probably easier for him to snatch one from me than fish one up himself!
Bull Chieftain: Juan-Yun, you're too lecherous for your own good!
Sennosuke: Let's not start trouble. Juan-Yun, if you want, I could find another girl for you, just as beautiful.
Sennosuke: But this here is my business. How 'bout you let me get on with it and save yourself some trouble. Nothing personal, kid.
Sennosuke: Take them away!
Juan-Yun: Not so fast!
Juan-Yun: If you're innocent, then you won't mind me saying something first.
Juan-Yun: Everyone knows how prosperous, how generous Sennosuke is. Well, has anyone ever stopped to think where all his money comes from?
Panther Chieftain: Enough with the jokes, boy. That money has been earned, fair and square! Sennosuke is an honest businessman!
Juan-Yun: An honest businessman...
Juan-Yun: So, for example, selling precious herbs that should only grow in Leopard Tribe territory is honest?
Panther Chieftain: Th-That...
Sennosuke: What, that!? And here I was thinking you had some real dirt on me!
Sennosuke: I lent the leopards some money once. They didn't have enough to pay it back, so they gave me access to some of their land instead.
Sennosuke: I've got nothing to hide there. You can ask them, if you want.
Juan-Yun: Himawari told me the same thing once.
Juan-Yun: But you know me, I've been out and about enough to hear stories.
Sennosuke: Oh, stories~ What a fun young pup our little lord is.
Sennosuke: Well then, if you don't mind, why not share one of these stories with us?
Juan-Yun: Gladly. Story is, you tricked the leopards into borrowing money and digging themselves into a debt they couldn't get out of.
Juan-Yun: And as repayment you took their most profitable mountain territory, essentially forcing them out of the East Alliance entirely!
Sennosuke: Ah, what a colorful story that was! Don't you all agree?
Panther Chieftain: Very interesting! Total nonsense, of course, but interesting!
Juan-Yun: Hold on, I'm not done.
Juan-Yun: So then I heard the east's only demihuman trade union—The Kai-Tai Group,
Juan-Yun: was totally extorted and ultimately torn apart by you and your thugs.
Tindoiimu: (Demihuman trade union... that must be what Baa Baa was talking about...)
Tindoiimu: (Come to think of it, the qilin checked the area afterward, and didn't find any sign of Baa Baa...)
Juan-Yun: And now the mermaids, living on the outskirts of the East Alliance, minding their own business. They fell right into your trap, didn't they?
Hestia: Mmmmph!?
Juan-Yun: Make them borrow money from you, make them unable to pay it back, then force them into servitude.
Juan-Yun: Now, if they're not being sold off for their medicinal scales, then it's for their beauty, off to Hot Spring Street...
Pang: And the Alliance does nothing about it!
Maeok: This... I...

Sennosuke: That's alright, arbiter, I'll handle this. 
Listen, little lord—debts are debts. They have to be repaid somehow.
Sennosuke: Those people borrowed money from me, they signed a contract. But some kind of extortion ring? That's nonsense!
Maeok: Sennosuke is right. If you have no proof, Juan-Yun...
Pang: What does it matter if he has proof? With stories like those, why didn't any of you investigate!?
Maeok: Well... leopards and demihumans? I mean...
Bull Chieftain: With that sort of riff-raff, of course we're going to believe the honey badgers.
Panther Chieftain: Sennosuke has assisted the Alliance through a great number of issues, at his own expense!
Seahorse Chieftain: Oh, I can't stand those mermaids! They're obviously demihumans, but they ask for territory like they have a right to it!
Pang: You...
Pang: Arbiter Maeok, is this how you feel, too?
Pang: You know these 'stories' the qilin lord has told are true, don't you? You just don't want to admit it!
Maeok: ......
Pang: ...So much time has passed since Yao, yet nothing has changed!
Pang: Still as corrupt as ever!
Pang: I knew I shouldn't have come back!
Pang: I'm bringing you back to Maple Lake!
Sennosuke: Oh yeah? You think you can take them from me?
Pang: I do! I won't let you touch another hair on their heads!
Sennosuke: Nice moves. If only you were a bit smarter.
Sennosuke: What do you all think about this? Robbery, plain and simple, no?
Panther Chieftain: Soldiers, apprehend this man!
Maeok: And who are you to summon our soldiers without my consent?
Tortoise Chieftain: Well, would you look at that! Our arbiter actually standing up for herself? I guess she's all grown up~
Panther Chieftain: This is an alliance, isn't it? We all have equal say! And since we're older, I'd say we have even more say than you, Maeok!
Maeok: You...!
Pang: (Ugh... I could run, but Puggi and Hestia...)
Shun: Traitor! You finally show your face!
Maeok: General Shun!?
Shun: Maeok, don't let Pang run away again, the damn backstabber...
Maeok: Pang...!? You mean, Prince Yao's cohort?
Sennosuke: Well, I'll be damned. I thought you looked like an honest one, but I guess you're a criminal, after all.
Pang: (...Damn! I'm done for...)
Yan-Bo: Come to an impasse~ seek her out. Assist you, she will.
Pang: (Oh yeah! I've still got that bag Yan-Bo gave me!)
Pang: Arbiter, I have something from your old friend, Yan-Bo. He wanted me to give this to you.
Maeok: Yan-Bo!?
Pang: —Here.
Maeok: That is... the holy talisman!?
Pang: This!? But, how!?
Shun: So you were the one who killed General Shun and ran off with our talisman! I should have known!
Pang: No, I never...
Shun: That talisman was specially made from Udumbara bark.
Shun: I know it when I see it! Impossible to counterfeit!
Juan-Yun: Wait, arbiter! Something's not right, here... Please, let me investigate.
Shun: Investigate what!? You think the holy talisman just flew right into his pocket?
Panther Chieftain: If I didn't know any better, I'd say this traitor and the qilin lord are in cahoots! They came here together, didn't they!?
Shun: What!? Is that true!?
Juan-Yun: Please, let me explain. It's because...
Shun: What is there to explain!?
Maeok: Silence!
Maeok: All this bickering will get us nowhere! I cannot turn the fugitive over directly to you, Shun.
Shun: Arbiter!
Maeok: Your arbiter has spoken! Soldiers, lock them up!
Juan-Yun: Arbiter, but...
Maeok: Silence! I'll question you later.
Sennosuke: Well that was fun! If there's nothing else, then I'll be taking these two home with me.
Sennosuke: Arbiter? What are you doing?
Maeok: If these two are truly with the fugitive, they'll need to be put on trial. I'm sorry, but we'll need your cooperation, honey badgers.
Pang: I've done this all on my own accord! They had no part in this!
Maeok: Take them away!
Sennosuke: ...Partners in crime, huh? Well, good luck, then.
Sennosuke: Everyone else, let's do tea soon.
Panther Chieftain: Of course, of course.
